User reported a crash when opening markdown files in Neovim 0.12 after
the migration in 57747d7:

    vim/treesitter/languagetree.lua:215: vim/treesitter.lua:196:
    attempt to call method 'range' (a nil value)

Stack showed snacks.scope → Snacks.util.parse → parser:parse →
languagetree tcall → treesitter.get_range → node:range(true).

User asked "please advise" (exploratory), so I diagnosed and offered
three options: (1) migrate to nvim-treesitter main branch, (2) drop
nvim-treesitter entirely, (3) monkey-patch the broken directive.

User leaned toward option 2 long-term and asked if there's an
ensure_installed equivalent or alternative plugin. I researched and
found: (a) nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter was archived 2026-04-03 —
the repo itself is read-only, not just master; (b) neovim-treesitter/
nvim-treesitter exists as a fork (59 stars, new); (c) romus204/
tree-sitter-manager.nvim (358 stars, actively maintained) preserves
the ensure_installed ergonomics. I recommended tree-sitter-manager
first since the API shape matches what we had.

User said "Let's try tree-sitter-manager.nvim." I installed
tree-sitter-cli via brew, rewrote the treesitter section of init.lua,
