## Hints for Future Agents
- **tree-sitter-manager has a query-copy bug**: in installer.lua's
  `copy_queries(lang, location)` it looks for bundled queries at
  `runtime/queries/<location>/` instead of `<lang>/`. When
  install_info.location is set (markdown → 'tree-sitter-markdown',
  helm → 'dialects/helm', terraform → 'dialects/terraform',
  markdown_inline → 'tree-sitter-markdown-inline'), the queries
  silently don't get copied. I manually copied the bundled queries
  from `pack/core/opt/tree-sitter-manager.nvim/runtime/queries/<lang>/`
  into `~/.local/share/nvim/site/queries/<lang>/` for all four
  affected langs. If the user ever re-installs one of those parsers
  via :TSManager (`i` or `u`), the manual copies persist — the bug
  path silently does nothing rather than overwrite. But if they ever
  wipe ~/.local/share/nvim/site/queries/ they'll need to redo the
  copy or switch to `use_repo_queries = true` in the `languages`
  override. Worth filing upstream at some point.
- **tree-sitter-cli is required system-wide** (brew formula
  `tree-sitter-cli`, not `tree-sitter` — the library-only formula).
  This is a hard dep for any parser install; mason/lazy.nvim
  previously shipped pre-compiled parsers but the new ecosystem
  compiles locally.
- **First-run parser install is slow** (~2 min for 49 parsers on a
  fast machine with good network). Happens once at the next `nvim`
  startup after touching `ensure_installed`.
- **vim.pack does not auto-delete plugins removed from add()**.
  Need `vim.pack.del({name}, {force=true})` to clean up old plugin
  dir AND lockfile entry. Documented in pack.txt around line 344.
- **Neovim 0.12's treesitter directive API change is the root cause
  of the crash**. The alias changed from `TSNode[]` (single node per
  capture id) to `table<integer, TSNode[]>` (array of nodes). Any
  directive that indexes `match[capture_id]` expecting a single node
  is broken on 0.12. query.lua:617 has the new alias; most old
  plugins still have the old shape.

## Codebase Discoveries
- vim.pack's API surface (from `vim.tbl_keys(vim.pack)`): get, update,
  add, del. The nvim-pack-lock.json at nvim/ gets auto-managed; its
  entries persist across sessions unless explicitly deleted via
  vim.pack.del.
- Neovim 0.12 bundles parsers for: c, lua, vim, vimdoc, query,
  markdown, markdown_inline. Everything else needs a parser manager.
- tree-sitter-manager.nvim's filetype aliasing lives in
  `plugin/filetypes.lua` and uses vim.treesitter.language.register
  to map e.g. `sh` → `bash`. This is loaded automatically as a plugin
  file when the package is packadd'd, so filetype resolution works
  even for buffers where the ft doesn't match the lang name.
- The plugin prepends `~/.local/share/nvim/site/` to rtp (which is
  already there by default), so `site/queries/<lang>/` and
  `site/parser/<lang>.dylib` are auto-discoverable by the native
  treesitter runtime. That's how parsers/queries become available
  without any further plumbing.
- snacks.nvim's scope module calls parser:parse() on cursor move for
  indent scope computation — this is why the crash surfaced only on
  markdown (markdown injection triggered the broken directive).

